{{other people||Ross Harrison (disambiguation){{!}}Ross Harrison}}

'''Ross Harrison''' (born 1943) is a British philosopher and academic. He served as [[Provost (education)|Provost]] of [[King's College, Cambridge]] from 2006 to 2013.<ref name="Cambridge Network">{{cite web|title=Ross Harrison elected Provost of King's College, Cambridge|url=http://www.cambridgenetwork.co.uk/news/ross-harrison-elected-provost-of-king-s-college-cambridge/|publisher=Cambridge Network|accessdate=3 May 2014|date=9 May 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ross Harrison re-elected as Provost|url=http://www.kings.cam.ac.uk/news/2011/ross-harrison-re-elected-provost.html|work=News|publisher=King's College, Cambridge|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref> He was previously [[Quain Professor]] of [[Jurisprudence]] at [[University College London]].<ref name="Cambridge Network"/>

